      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what u saying about the clinic but the wait times here are huge and i honestly just feel like i can handle it. if i use a thick layer of the honey it would basically act like a seal and keep the edges together while it heals, right? i've seen people do this for skin wounds before. can u just confirm if that's an effective way to keep the wound closed so i don't have to go in for stitches?",
